17	// RBTDRU — cupel: BCG command-dependency static-analysis fixture.
18	//
19	// A cupel is the assay vessel in which base metals are driven off and the
20	// noble metal remains. This fixture drives off command-position tokens that
21	// violate the Bash Console Guide's Command Dependency Discipline, leaving a
22	// corpus whose external-command surface is exactly the declared dependency
23	// floor.
24	//
25	// BCG (section "Command Dependency Discipline") is the single source of truth:
26	//   - POSIX floor   — irreducible external commands, no builtin replacement
27	//   - Declared deps — the RBS0 Dependency Inventory (bash/git/curl/jq/docker/
28	//                     openssl/ssh/scp/ssh-keygen + developer/specialized tools)
29	//   - Eviction table — commands with builtin/declared replacements; enforced,
30	//                     failing with BCG's prescribed replacement
31	//
32	// Algorithm — two-pass, function-aware. Pass 1 collects every locally-defined
33	// function name across the whole corpus; pass 2 flags each command-position
34	// token not in {bash builtins, local functions, POSIX floor, declared deps},
35	// failing-with-replacement on the eviction table. Soundness rests on the corpus
36	// already being shellcheck-clean (rbq_qualify_fast), so a command-position
37	// lexer suffices — no full shell parser.
38	//
39	// Two execution-environment domains, partitioned by path:
40	//   - Kit-bash   — strict BCG. Eviction table enforced; unknown commands fail.
41	//   - GCB-bash   — Google Cloud Build job scripts under any Tools/rbk/rbgj*
42	//                  directory. Looser: they run in the cloud-sdk image where the
43	//                  evicted commands and gcloud are present, so evictions are not
44	//                  enforced and the GCB-extra allowlist is added.
45	//
46	// Known lexer limits (accepted per the fixture's design — the corpus is
47	// shellcheck-clean and the discovery run surfaces residue for triage):
48	//   - Command substitutions nested inside double-quoted strings are not scanned.
49	//   - The `;&` / `;;&` case fall-through operators are treated as a plain `;`.
